manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Amazon Basics High-Capacity Rechargeable Batteries, AA, AAA Reliable Performance Enjoy dependable power with Amazon Basics High-Capacity rechargeable batteries. Available in a multiple types (AA, AAA) and pack sizes for your needs. More Power for Devices Ideal for professional or everyday use, high-capacity batteries (AA 2400 mAh; AAA 850 mAh) are a great choice for both high- and low-drain devices. Long Battery Life Providing an extremely gradual self-discharge, these long-lasting batteries retain majority capacity for 12 months and 80% capacity for 24 months. Pre-Charged, Ready to Use The rechargeable batteries come pre-charged and ready to use right out of the box. They can be recharged hundreds of times with minimal power loss.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Eco-Friendly Power Solution: Unveiling the Pros and Cons of Amazon Basics AAA Rechargeable Batteries
reviews.reviewText: As a tech enthusiast and a frequent user of various battery-powered devices, I've had the opportunity to test the Amazon Basics 16-Pack Rechargeable AAA NiMH High-Capacity Batteries (850 mAh). Here's my detailed review, based on my personal experience and observations.Pros:+ Wide Compatibility: These batteries are compatible with a broad range of devices, from high to low drain, making them versatile for different uses around the house.+ Pre-Charged Convenience: The batteries arrive pre-charged, ready for immediate use. This feature is incredibly convenient, eliminating the need for initial charging.+ Rechargeable and Eco-Friendly: With the ability to be recharged up to 500 times with minimal power loss, these batteries are not only cost-effective but also environmentally friendly.+ Low Self-Discharge Rate: The batteries maintain 80% capacity for up to 24 months, allowing for long-term storage without significant power loss.+ Frustration-Free Packaging: The packaging is easy to open and access the batteries without any hassle or excessive waste.Cons:- Inconsistent Lifespan: Some users have reported that the batteries' lifespan falls short of expectations. The batteries seem to provide fewer recharge cycles than claimed, with some users noting a significant decline in performance after about 120 cycles.- Variable Pre-Charge Levels: Although the batteries are supposed to come pre-charged, some users have reported that they needed to charge them for several hours before reaching full capacity.- Potential Fit Issues: The positive end of these batteries is slightly smaller than standard batteries, which may cause fit issues in some devices.- Voltage Limitations: These batteries have a voltage of 1.2V, which may not be compatible with all devices. Some devices may inaccurately indicate that the battery is low or half-charged, even when it's fully charged.- Inconsistent Performance: Some users have reported a decline in performance over time, with batteries needing to be swapped out more frequently after a few months of use.- Leakage Issues: A few users have reported leakage issues, with batteries discharging a white powdery substance when stored for extended periods.In conclusion, the Amazon Basics 16-Pack Rechargeable AAA NiMH High-Capacity Batteries (850 mAh) offer a mix of convenience and performance, with a few potential drawbacks. They're a solid choice for those seeking an environmentally friendly, cost-effective solution for powering their devices. However, users should be aware of the potential for inconsistent performance and lifespan, and ensure they're suitable for their specific devices and usage patterns.
